text: The Inatsisartut (), also known as the Parliament of Greenland in English, is the unicameral parliament (legislative branch) of Greenland.* * * It was created in 1979, it meets in Inatsisartut, on the islet of Nuuk Center in central Nuuk. There are 31 members. They are elected for four-year periods. ==References== Category:Politics of Denmark Greenland Greenland Category:Organizations based in Greenland
title: Inatsisartut
